st - simple terminal
--------------------
st is a simple terminal emulator for X which sucks less.
git clone git://git.suckless.org/st

Looking for a nice color? Here's a one-liner to print colormap.
for i in {0..255}; do print -Pn "%K{$i}  %k%F{$i}${(l:3::0:)i}%f " ${${(M)$((i%6)):#3}:+$'\n'}; done


Requirements
------------
In order to build st you need the Xlib header files.
yay -S libxft-bgra     # for emoji
pacamn -S xdg-utils    # open files by type(buggy use mimeo instead)
pacman -S xclip        # copy to clipboard in term
yay -S mimeo           # open files by type, settings in vim /home/ihar/.config/mimeo/associations.txt
yay -S xdg-utils-mimeo # replace xdg-open with mimeo (xdg  1.1.3-3 bugs if use in ST)

#define MODKEY Mod1Mask // ALT, use xmodmap - to check settings
#define TERMMOD (Mod1Mask|ShiftMask)

Patches
----------
Mouse and kbd scroll in st history
https://st.suckless.org/patches/scrollback/st-scrollback-20200419-72e3f6c.diff
https://st.suckless.org/patches/scrollback/st-scrollback-mouse-20191024-a2c479c.diff
https://st.suckless.org/patches/scrollback/st-scrollback-mouse-altscreen-20200416-5703aa0.diff
https://st.suckless.org/patches/scrollback/st-scrollback-mouse-increment-0.8.2.diff
    { XK_ANY_MOD,           Button4, kscrollup,      {.i = mousescrollincrement },	0, /* !alt */ -1 },
	{ XK_ANY_MOD,           Button5, kscrolldown,    {.i = mousescrollincrement },	0, /* !alt */ -1 },
    to scrool by mouse no need shift

    { ShiftMask,            XK_Page_Up,     kscrollup,      {.i = -1} },
	{ ShiftMask,            XK_Page_Down,   kscrolldown,    {.i = -1} },
	{ ShiftMask,            XK_Up,     	    kscrollup,      {.i =  1} },
	{ ShiftMask,            XK_Down,   	    kscrolldown,    {.i =  1} },

Open new st hotkey
https://st.suckless.org/patches/newterm/st-newterm-0.8.2.diff
    { MODKEY,               XK_n,           newterm,        {.i =  0} },

Open contents of the clipboard in a user-defined browser.
https://st.suckless.org/patches/open_copied_url/st-openclipboard-20190202-3be4cf1.diff
    { MODKEY,               XK_w,           opencopied,     {.v =  def_opener} }, // open in memeo file in cb

Delete empty space under st window
https://st.suckless.org/patches/anysize/st-anysize-0.8.4.diff

Support w3m images hack
https://st.suckless.org/patches/w3m/st-w3m-0.8.3.diff

Externalpipe
Reading and writing st's screen through a pipe
https://st.suckless.org/patches/externalpipe/st-externalpipe-0.8.4.diff
Reading and writing st's screen history from scrollback patch
https://st.suckless.org/patches/externalpipe/st-externalpipe-eternal-0.8.3.diff
open st hist in vim
https://st.suckless.org/patches/externalpipe/editscreen.sh
gets all urls from st hist and show in dmenu
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LukeSmithxyz/st/master/st-urlhandler
open dmenu of all cmds from hist
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LukeSmithxyz/st/master/st-copyout



st-url-mouse-click.diff

Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (st is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install st (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running st
----------
If you did not install st with make clean install, you must compile
the st terminfo entry with the following command:

    tic -sx st.info

See the man page for additional details.

